/PL781/XXREADINGS: TORAH STUDY/XX/PR

/KATORAH STUDY/XX/PR

Somewhere out of time/PR

In the mystery of time/PR

Somewhere between memory and forgetfulness,/PR

Dimly though/PR

I remember how once I stood/PR

at Your mountain trembling/PR

Amid the fire and the thunder./PR

How I stood there, out of bondage/PR

In a strange land and afraid./PR

And You loved me and You fed me/PR

And I feasted on Your words./PR

And, yes, I can remember/PR

How the thunder was my heart/PR

And the fire was my soul./PR

God, I do remember./PR

The fire burns in me anew./PR

And here I am once more/PR

A witness to that timeless moment./PR

Present now in the light of Your Torah/PR

I am reborn./PR

Nancy Lee Gossels/XX/PR

