When I was a boy and fancy free,/PR

my folks had no fine clothes for me./PR

All I got was words:/PR

/ITGot tsu danken/XX    (Thank God)/PR

/ITZoln mir lebn un zeyn gezunt./XX    (We should live and be well)/PR

/PR

When I was wont to travel far,/PR

They didnòt provide for me a car./PR

All I got was words:/PR

/ITGey gezunt/XX    (Go in health)/PR

/ITGey palmelekh/XX    (Go slowly)/PR

/ITHob a gliklekhe rayse./XX    (Have a good trip)/PR

/PR

I wanted to increase my knowledge/PR

But they couldnòt send me to college./PR

All I got was words:/PR

/ITHob seykhel/XX    (Have common sense)/PR

/ITZey nisht keyn nar/XX    (Donòt be a fool)/PR

/ITToyreh iz di beste skhoyre./XX    (Torah is the best merchandise)/PR

/PR

The years have flown,/PR

the world has turned,/PR

things Iòve gotten, things Iòve learned,/PR

Yet I remember/PR

/ITZog dem emes/XX    (Tell the truth)/PR

/ITGib tsedukeh/XX    (Give /ITtzedakah/XX)/PR

/ITHob rakhmones/XX    (Have compassion)/PR

/ITZey a mensch!/XX    (Be a mensch!)/PR

