/PL787/XXREADINGS: PRELUDES TO KADDISH/XX/PR

/KAPRELUDES TO KADDISH/PR

Dirge Without Music/XX/PR

I am not resigned to the shutting away of loving hearts in the/PR


hard ground./PR

So it is, and so it will be, for so it has been, time out of mind:/PR

Into the darkness they go, the wise and the lovely. Crowned/PR

With lilies and with laurel they go; but I am not resigned./PR

/PR

Lovers and thinkers, into the earth with you./PR

Be one with the dull, the indiscriminate dust./PR

A fragment of what you felt, of what you knew,/PR

A formula, a phrase remains, but the best is lost./PR

/PR

The answers quick and keen, the honest look, the laughter,/PR


the love,/PR

They are gone. They are gone to feed the roses. Elegant and/PR


curled/PR

Is the blossom. Fragrant is the blossom. I know. But I do not/PR


approve./PR

More precious was the light in your eyes than all the roses in/PR


the world./PR

/PR

Down, down, down into the darkness of the grave/PR

Gently they go, the beautiful, the tender, the kind;/PR

Quietly they go, the intelligent, the witty, the brave./PR

I know. But I do not approve. And I am not resigned./PR

Edna St. Vincent Millay/XX/PR

