/PL789/XXREADINGS: PRELUDES TO KADDISH/XX/PR

/KAIn Many Houses/XX/PR

In many houses/PR

all at once/PR

I see my mother and father/PR

and they are young/PR

as they walk in./PR

/PR

Why should my/PR

tears come,/PR

to see them laughing?/PR

/PR

That they cannot/PR

see me/PR

is of no matter:/PR

/PR

I was once/PR

their dream:/PR

now/PR

they are mine./PR

Diane Cole/XX/PR

/PR

To open eyes when others close them/PR

to hear when others do not wish to listen/PR

to look when others turn away/PR

to seek to understand when others give up/PR

to rouse oneself when others accept/PR

to continue the struggle even when one is not the strongest/PR

to cry out when others keep silent--/PR

to be a Jew/PR

it is that,/PR

it is first of all that/PR

and further/PR

to live when others are dead/PR

and to remember when others have forgotten./PR

Emmanuel Eydoux (translated from the French by Jonathan Magonet)/XX/PR

