/PGREADINGS: PRELUDES TO KADDISH/XX794/XX/PR

/KATo My Father/XX/PR

You gathered incredible strength/PR

in order to die/PR

to seem calm and fully conscious/PR

without complaint, without trembling/PR

without a cry/PR

so that I would not be afraid/PR

/PR

Your wary hand/PR

slowly grew cold in mine/PR

and guided me carefully/PR

beyond into the house of death/PR

so I might come to know it/PR

/PR

Thus in the past you used to take my hand/PR

and guide me through the world/PR

and show me life/PR

so I would not fear/PR

/PR

I will follow after you/PR

confident as a child/PR

toward the silent country/PR

where you went first/PR

so I would not feel a stranger there/PR

/PR

And I will not be afraid./PR

Blaga Dmitrova/XX/PR

