Healing is both an exercise/PR

and an understanding/PR

and yet not of the will/PR

nor of the intention/PR

It is a wisdom/PR

and a deeper knowledge/PR

of the daily swing/PR

of life and death/PR

in all creation/PR

There is defeat/PR

to overcome/PR

and acceptance of living/PR

to be established/PR

and always/PR

there must be hope/PR

Not hope of healing/PR

but the hope which informs/PR

the coming moment/PR

and gives it reason/PR

The hope which is/PR

each manòs breath/PR

the certainty of love/PR

and of loving/PR

Death may live/PR

in the living/PR

and healing rise/PR

in the dying/PR

for whom the natural end/PR

is part of the gathering/PR

and of the harvest/PR

to be expected/PI/PR

